## 5. Do & Don't Language

This is your daily reference. Check your language against this table.

| ✅ Do Say | ❌ Don't Say |
|-----------|-------------|
| "We'll guide you" | "You must comply" |
| "When you're ready" | "Before it's too late" |
| "Peace of mind" | "Avoid legal disaster" |
| "Helps your family" | "Protects your family from confusion" |
| "Simple steps" | "Easy process" |
| "Your wishes, documented" | "Testamentary dispositions" |
| "Let's get started" | "Commence the process" |
| "Your will is saved" | "Document successfully stored" |
| "Update anytime" | "Amendments may be made" |
| "Something went wrong" | "An error has occurred" |
| "We decided to..." | "A decision has been made to..." |
| "Here's what happens next" | "The subsequent process involves..." |

### Always Use Active Voice

We always take responsibility for our actions. Active voice tells people who's doing what. Passive voice hides responsibility.

| Passive (Don't) | Active (Do) |
|-----------------|-------------|
| "A decision has been made to close your account" | "We've decided to close your account" |
| "Your request is being processed" | "We're processing your request" |
| "The document was not saved" | "We couldn't save your document" |

### Positive Framing

Instead of focusing on what could go wrong, emphasise what goes right:

| ❌ Negative | ✅ Positive |
|------------|------------|
| "If you don't plan..." | "When you plan..." |
| "Avoid disputes" | "Keep things clear" |
| "Don't let your family struggle" | "Make life easier for your family" |

