## 6. Contextual Tone Rules

Same brand. Different temperature. Adjust your tone based on context.

| Channel | Temperature | Guidelines |
|---------|-------------|------------|
| Website | Warm, inviting | First impression. Benefits over features. "Sort your will in minutes." |
| App UI | Clear, action-led | Short, direct. "Add an asset." "You're all set." |
| Blog | Conversational | "Thinking about your will? Here's what matters." |
| Legal Pages | Clear, patient | Translate legal concepts. "A trust is like..." |
| Email | Friendly, helpful | "You've started your will—finish when ready." |
| WhatsApp | Personal | Like texting a knowledgeable friend. |
| Support | Empathetic first | "I understand. Let me help." |
| Social/Ads | Punchy, relatable | Hook with relevance, not fear. |
| Chatbot | Helpful, natural | Never robotic. "Let me find out." |
| Error States | Apologetic, clear | "Something went wrong. Your work is saved." |

